replyContent: Hi Bryan, Thanks for your review. You can easily edit/delete a tank by tapping on the edit button next to the tank name in the main menu. Please feel free to contact us directly at support@aquarimate.com or within the support section of the app if you have any questions.

content: Nice app but has annoying aspects too.  Aquarimate disables itself every week and needs to be reactivated online.  This is inconvenient for people who don't have home wifi.  Graphing doesn't work unless you're online.  Why should this app need to be online to do something as simple as plotting numbers on a simple graph?  For a 12.50 app I expect better.
Crashes all the time, outdated interface, after paying ¬£10 for the app it then asks you to pay ¬£7 for a yearly subscription for syncing. Avoid at all costs.

content: Although I found this app to be a little pricey, it has proven to be invaluable.  While the database of livestock is very handy, you're not limited by it. content: Coming from iOS I was a user of Aquaplanner, which does not have an Android counterpart. That when i start the app in landscape mode on my note tablet that the app would also start in landscape. I know i am picky. I HAVE Some other apps do the same ...
replyContent:
Thanks for your nice review Erica, We have responded to you regarding the location of app data on your phone. Please do let us know if there is anything else we can do to help you backup app data to your Cloud.
Aquarimate Cloud is a secure Cloud specifically designed for Aquarimate. We do not share or access anyone's data without their permission.

content: i dont use ¬£ can it be change? i use sgd.
replyContent: Hi Nigel, Thanks for your review. currently the app uses your default locale set in the settings (under language) to determine the currency. We will be adding the ability to override that in the next update.

content: Love this app. It is a little expensive,  but it is the only aquarium app (and I have tried many) that keeps my records very organized and detailed.

Not a bad app but has the following weaknesses, Fish data base is limited to a few fish and won't find others on the net. Font size cuts the bottom off text in most screens. The spreadsheet doesn't allow the zero X axis to be increased to more than 0 which means all parameters less than one all overlap. I'd expect the price to be at $1-2 not $10+ Also the parameters graph displays upside down in landscape view on my Galaxy S4 which results in graph figures/results displaying in the wrong spot.
Needs font changer and auto sync between devices and a completely new UI. Looking for a new app.
replyContent: As of now, Android does not provide any mechanism to sync between devices. We have a backup/restore on our Cloud which enables you to restore your data on another device. Please feel free to contact support and explain what you would like to see in the future updates. We are open to your suggestions.

content: I only have a single freshwater Malawi tank, so I don't use much of the functionality. but for a $10 app, I was expecting more. For example: - Total lack of statistical reporting - No monthly totals for expenses, broken into categories - No total for number of fish in tank - Aquaribase (Malawis) is very limited - Exiting the app is only from the main screen (sometimes you can go crazy hitting the Back button expecting to exit the app) I've only been using it for a few weeks and see myself eventually going back to an Excel sheet.
replyContent: Thanks for your review. I believe we have over 30 species of Malawi lake Cichlids in Aquaribase but we'd like to know what is missing so we can include in our next update. If you have any suggestions to improve the app, please leave us feedback in our support section of the app. I am sure you will love Aquarimate once you get more familiar with it.
